# Python Standards

## Layout

- Business logic in `src/` (`bbb_classifier`, `bbb_geo`, `bbb_dataset`, `boltzgen_design`).
- CLIs: `bbb-classifier` and `bbb-geo` entry points (`python -m bbb_classifier`, `python -m bbb_geo`).
- Configs live in `configs/` (YAML). Do not hardcode experiment hyperparameters in Python.

## Style (enforced by CI)

- Ruff: line length 100, target py311. Run `make lint` / `make format`.
- Use `from __future__ import annotations` in new modules.
- Prefer `@dataclass` for config/threshold structs; type hints on public APIs.
- First-party imports: `bbb_classifier`, `bbb_geo`, `boltzgen_design`, `bbb_dataset`.

## Type checking

- Mypy runs on `packages/boltzgen_design`, `packages/dataset/src`, `packages/bbb_models/src`.
- `packages/boltzgen/` is excluded (upstream submodule). Do not lint/format boltzgen unless explicitly asked.

## Tests

- Pytest paths: `packages/bbb_models/tests`, `packages/dataset/tests`, `packages/boltzgen_design/tests`.
- Dataset package requires ≥85% coverage. Run `make test` or `uv run pytest -q`.

## Example CLI usage

```bash
uv run bbb-classifier train --exp configs/experiments/exp03_esm_tab_mlp.yaml
uv run bbb-geo train --exp configs/experiments/exp09_struct_egnn_noise.yaml
```
